   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER EIGHT THE EXERCISE OF OUR SPIRIT Scripture Reading: 2 Tim 1:6-7; Rom 8:5-6; Heb 4:12 OUTLINE To fan our spirit 2 Tim 1:6-7: God has not given us a spirit of cowardice, but of power, love, and sobermindedness.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Our spirit is surrounded by the three parts of the soul will, emotion, and mind: Our will should be strong, full of power.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Our emotion should be loving, full of love.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Our mind should be sober, full of sobermindedness.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>To set our mind on the spirit Rom 8:5-6: To set our mind on the flesh is death.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>To set our mind on the spirit is life and peace.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>To discern our spirit from our soul Heb 4:12.</S>
   </TEXT>
